author: Michelle Doll Olson
cuisine: North America
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/beef-ragu-spaghetti-5e7b758b54d63c4d8436eb42
---

Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry all produce. Trim and quarter @zucchini{1}(trimmed and quartered lengthwise); cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick pieces. Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, and diced). Mince @garlic{2%cloves}(minced).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground beef{10%oz} and season with half the @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp} (you'll use the rest later), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat.

> TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Transfer beef to a plate.

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%oz} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Carefully reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water (¾ cup for 4 servings), then drain.

While spaghetti cooks, heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tsp} in pan used for beef over medium-high heat. Add zucchini and onion. Cook, stirring, until softened, ~{5-7%minutes}. Stir in garlic and remaining Italian seasoning; cook until garlic is fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add beef, @crushed tomatoes{13.76%oz can}, @beef stock concentrate{1}, and reserved pasta cooking water to pan with veggies. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer until thick and saucy, ~{5-10%minutes}.

> TIP: If mixture begins to stick to the bottom of the pan, stir in a splash of water.

Taste and season with salt and pepper. Stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted.

Add spaghetti and @garlic herb butter{2%tbsp} to pan with ragù; toss to combine. Divide pasta between plates. Sprinkle with @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} and as many @?chili flakes{1%tsp} as you like. Serve.